Ellipsify truncates an element's text when a given character/word count is reached, appends an ellipsis and removes any subsequent siblings from the DOM.

Optional arguments:
	count: number - supply a character/word count for Ellipsify to use as the break point where text will be truncated and an ellipsis will be appended (25 is the default count value)   
	type: 'string' - "chars" or "words" - tell Ellipsify to truncate text based on character or word count (word count is the default)  

Use:

	Default:

		$('p').Ellipsify();
	
		- will truncate text in the <p> containing the 25th word, append an ellipsis and remove any subsequent <p> tags in the jQuery object from the DOM
	
	Count argument:

		$('p').Ellipsify({
			count:75
		});
	
		- will truncate text in the <p> containing the 75th word, append an ellipsis and remove any subsequent <p> tags in the jQuery object from the DOM

	Type argument:

		$('p').Ellipsify({
			type:'chars'
		});
	
		- will truncate text in the <p> containing the 25th character, append an ellipsis and remove any subsequent <p> tags in the jQuery object from the DOM
	
	Count and Type arguments:

		$('p').Ellipsify({
			count:500,
			type:'chars'
		});
	
		- will truncate text in the <p> containing the 500th character, append an ellipsis and remove any subsequent <p> tags in the jQuery object from the DOM
	
